A Turdus grayi is a species of bird from the thrush family, found in Central America and parts of Mexico. 
Its feathers are mainly gray with a white belly and dark wings. 
The beak is yellow and the eyes are large and dark. 
The texture of the feathers is smooth and sleek. 
The body is slender with a slightly curved posture. 
Turdus grayi is commonly found in humid forests and tropical gardens where it feeds on insects and fruits. 
They are known for their melodious songs and are sometimes kept as pets.
